{\par \b Syntax:}\par zeros(Expr,[Var])\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the zeros (reals or complex according to the CAS settings) of the expression Expr for the variable Var (or the matrix where the lines are the solutions of the system : Expr1=0,Expr2=0...).\par
{\par \b Example:}\par zeros(x^2+4) returns [] in real mode and [-2*i,2*i] in complex mode\par }